description.narrative: By October 2019, a total of 8,266 children (4,003 girls, 4,263 boys) out of school children participated in learning and a total of 7,204 pre-primary children (3,532 girls and 3,672 boys) at the right age (3–5 years) had accessed quality early learning in four underserved counties because of the increased capacity of 75 ECD county-level facilitators and 2,008 (1,104 females, 904 males) teachers/caregivers to interpret and apply the ECD policy and curriculum | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
